SW of Makiungu jct. Rolling hills & plains with cultivation & degraded grazing land. Shrubby weedy cover with Tapiphyllum obtusifolium, Dichrostachys, Croton, & diverse grasses & forbs such as Eragrostis, Oxygonum, Stylosanthes.
Goromonzi Dist.: Chinamora, Domboshowa Training School.

14½ km on Babati rd from Makiungu jct, then left to powerline, then 1½ km up the line. Rolling hills with a rich low woodland-bushland 3-5(-9)m: Brachystegia spiciformis, Combretum spp, Catunaregam, many other woody & herbaceous species.
Sumbawanga District, 29 km on Sumbawanga - Mpanda road.
Ruaha National Park, near Ruaha River at ranger post opposite Lunda.

Lusaka District, Nachitete: along Kafue Powerline; 8.5 km S along Chifwema Road; then 5 km E along Kafue Powerline Road, S-SE of Lusaka. Collections in remnant forest, along cultivations on limestone and quartz outcrops.
Abercorn-Mbeya road close to Siasi bridge.
Kasungu Dist., 30 mi. N of Kasungu on M1.
Darwin Dist.: near upper reaches of Nyatandi River.
On road outside Ruaha National Park boundary, 5 km beyond fork to Idodi. Acacia, Commiphora, Combretum bush with tetse flies.
